item.title: Global fleets steam into Sydney
item.description: Ships from nations including China, Thailand, the United States, Malaysia, France, Japan and former colonial power Britain passed through the heads into the famous Sydney Harbour where they joined 16 tall ships from around the world in preparation for a ceremonial fleet review on October 5, 2013.
item.ExtractedText: << Previous Â Next >> The HMAS Sydney passes the Sydney Opera House on October 4 as part of celebrations to commemorate 100 years since the Royal Australian Navy's fleet first entered the city's waters. Ships from nations including China, Thailand, the United States, Malaysia, France, Japan and Britain passed into the famous harbor, where they joined 16 tall ships from around the world in preparation for a ceremonial fleet review on October 5, 2013.
